"As a matter of fact, while new populations have been extensively established along the railway lines, and field after field has been appropriated for residential suburbs, the people and the houses have numerically decreased in the wide intervening expanses of rural territory. This effect has naturally been produced by restricting the cultivation almost exclusively to grass-crops; for it may be taken as a general rule, that where six men would be employed on a farm with a fair proportion of arable land. only two are"